AUDIO: 'Most professional video content requires a stack of tools, design software, motion graphics, and a video editor. But the video you\'re watching right now required none of them. It was generated and edited using AI. That\'s no Figma, no Photoshop, no After Effects, no'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Premiere, and no Final Cut. Everything you\'re seeing right now was generated from a single prompt. The lower thirds, the captions, the motion graphics, all made possible using Claude code and HyperFrames by HeyGen. And in this'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video, I\'m going to show you exactly how to build this yourself. Coming up. So, what is HyperFrames? It\'s an open-source framework built by HeyGen, designed to create and render videos,'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'motion graphics, and animated overlays directly from HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Now, if those three letters just triggered a cold sweat, I want you to breathe because you don\'t have to write any of that yourself. The AI does it all. HyperFrames is built specifically'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for AI agents. So, when you pair it with Claude code, it becomes something genuinely powerful. You describe what you want and it builds the visuals. I\'m talking lower thirds, animated captions, full motion sequences, all from a single'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt. And the best part is you don\'t need to be a developer to use any of this. All right, let\'s get you set up. But first, there are two things you need to install. That\'s Node.js and FFmpeg. Now, if you\'re a developer, you probably'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have an idea of what to do here. But if not, I\'ve left step-by-step instructions in the description. It\'s simpler than it sounds, I promise. Now, before we get into any commands and prompts, I want to show you how I set up my workspace. I created a dedicated folder for all AI'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'projects. Something like this. It keeps everything organized, and it gives Claude a clear workspace to operate inside, which makes the whole process run a lot more smooth. You\'re going to want to structure yours however works best for you, but this is just what'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'works for me. Now, two ways to get HyperFrames ready. Option one is you give Claude the HyperFrames GitHub repository and let it handle the entire setup. The prompt will look something like this. I want to use HyperFrames in this project. Here is the repository.'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then you include the HyperFrames repo link. I\'ll have that in the description. And then you can say set up everything needed so I can create preview and render videos. Claude reads the repository, install what\'s needed, and prepares your environment. Complete'

